<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-04-05T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-04-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="122" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d122">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">812.00/23543a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Guaymas</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Yost</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-04-05T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">April 5,
                                            1920—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Navy Department informs me that you have telegraphed Commander,
                                Pacific Fleet, requesting him to send war vessel to Guaymas.
                                Telegraph reason for your request, and report on present situation
                                in your district.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>